crossData

public static java.lang.Object[][] crossData(java.lang.Object[][] data1,
                                             java.lang.Object[][] data2,
                                             java.lang.Object[][]... dataN)
Creates a parameter array that crosses the data returned by two (possibly identical) dataProviders.

Parameters:
data1 - An Object[][] produced by one dataProvider
data2 - An Object[][] produced by a second dataProvider
dataN - Other Object[][] to cross
Returns:
An Object[][] such that, for each row, there exists a pair of rows from data1 and data2 that were concatenated to produce it.

nullable

public static java.lang.Object[][] nullable(java.lang.Object[][] data)
Creates a parameter array which includes all of data plus an addition Object[] containing only nulls. Check the first Object[] in data to determine array length. If there are no parameter arrays, or data is null, then the returned Object[][] will contain 1 parameter array: {null}.

Parameters:
data - An Object[][] produced by a dataProvider
Returns:
An Object[][] containing the parameter arrays in data plus a new parameter array with all nulls.
